@page "/blog/financial-wellness"
@attribute [AllowAnonymous]
@inherits BlogPostBase

<PageTitle>SmartBudget - Financial Wellness</PageTitle>

<link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/blog.css" />

<div class="blog-post-page">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="breadcrumb-container">
            <nav aria-label="Breadcrumb">
                <ol class="breadcrumb">
                    <li class="breadcrumb-item"><a href="/"><i class="bi bi-house-door"></i> Home</a></li>
                    <li class="breadcrumb-item"><i class="bi bi-chevron-right"></i></li>
                    <li class="breadcrumb-item"><a href="/blog">Blog</a></li>
                    <li class="breadcrumb-item"><i class="bi bi-chevron-right"></i></li>
                    <li class="breadcrumb-item active">Financial Wellness</li>
                </ol>
            </nav>
        </div>

        <article class="blog-post">
            <div class="post-header">
                <span class="post-category-badge">Lifestyle</span>
                <h1>Financial Wellness: How to Reduce Money Stress</h1>
                <div class="post-meta">
                    <span><i class="bi bi-person-circle"></i> Folake Adeyemi</span>
                    <span><i class="bi bi-calendar3"></i> @CurrentDate</span>
                    <span><i class="bi bi-clock"></i> 6 min read</span>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="post-body-content">
                <p>Financial stress affects your mental and physical health. This guide will help you improve your financial wellness and reduce money stress in @CurrentYear.</p>

                <h2>What is Financial Wellness?</h2>
                <p>Financial wellness means having a healthy relationship with money. It includes:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Feeling in control of your finances</li>
                    <li>Having a financial plan</li>
                    <li>Feeling confident about your financial decisions</li>
                    <li>Having a safety net for emergencies</li>
                </ul>

                <h2>Signs of Financial Stress</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li>Constantly worrying about money</li>
                    <li>Avoiding looking at your bank account</li>
                    <li>Difficulty sleeping due to financial concerns</li>
                    <li>Using credit cards for necessities</li>
                    <li>Feeling overwhelmed by debt</li>
                </ul>

                <h2>How to Reduce Financial Stress</h2>
                <h3>1. Know Your Numbers</h3>
                <p>Track your income and expenses. Use SmartBudget to get a clear picture of your finances.</p>

                <h3>2. Create a Budget</h3>
                <p>A budget gives you control. It helps you plan and avoid surprises.</p>

                <h3>3. Build an Emergency Fund</h3>
                <p>Having a financial safety net reduces anxiety about unexpected expenses.</p>

                <h3>4. Get Professional Help</h3>
                <p>Consider working with a financial advisor or credit counselor.</p>

                <h3>5. Practice Self-Care</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Exercise regularly</li>
                    <li>Practice mindfulness and meditation</li>
                    <li>Talk to someone about your financial concerns</li>
                    <li>Take breaks from financial planning</li>
                </ul>

                <div class="post-cta">
                    <h3>Reduce Your Financial Stress</h3>
                    <p>Take control of your finances with SmartBudget.</p>
                    <a href="/Account/Register" class="btn-cta">Get Started Free →</a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </article>
    </div>
</div>


@code {
    protected override async Task OnInitializedAsync()
    {
        PageName = "blog-post";
        await base.OnInitializedAsync();
    }
}